1
00:00:04,338 --> 00:00:06,006
[♪ rising music playing]

2
00:00:06,089 --> 00:00:09,968
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL - BAUDELAIRE

3
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:16,642
FOR ALL THE BOYS AND GIRLS
STRUGGLING THROUGH ADOLESCENCE

4
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,727
AND FOR THE BOYS AND GIRLS WE ONCE WERE

5
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:23,106
[bird trilling]

6
00:00:23,190 --> 00:00:26,485
[boy] <i>Ah, dear Baudelaire...</i>

7
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:28,528
<i>I am confined.</i>

8
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:33,659
<i>I am confined in this town
surrounded by mountains.</i>

9
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:36,578
[indistinct chatter]

10
00:00:36,662 --> 00:00:38,163
<i>Empty alleyways.</i>

11
00:00:38,247 --> 00:00:39,498
[student 1] Let's go to the arcade.

12
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:40,582
[boy] <i>Closed shutter doors.</i>

13
00:00:40,666 --> 00:00:42,167
[student 2] Did you catch GLAY's new song?

14
00:00:42,251 --> 00:00:43,752
[boy] <i>The boring route to school.</i>

15
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:45,170
[student 3] Can I burn it onto my MD?

16
00:00:45,254 --> 00:00:48,423
[boy] <i>Why is all the metal
in this town rusted?</i>

17
00:00:49,550 --> 00:00:51,426
<i>Why does this town...</i>

18
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:55,264
<i>suffocate me so badly?</i>

19
00:00:56,932 --> 00:00:58,600
<i>In the confinement of this town,</i>

20
00:00:59,101 --> 00:01:02,562
<i>literature is the only thing
that teaches me anything real.</i>

21
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:06,066
<i>And my only source of hope?</i>

22
00:01:08,527 --> 00:01:09,695
<i>That is...</i>

23
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:12,781
[laughter]

24
00:01:12,864 --> 00:01:15,117
[♪ soft music playing]

25
00:01:15,242 --> 00:01:16,243
<i>...an angel.</i>

26
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:17,327
[coach] On your marks.

27
00:01:17,411 --> 00:01:18,412
SAEKI

28
00:01:18,495 --> 00:01:21,123
- [blows whistle]
- [girls] Go, go!

29
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:22,249
[boy] <i>There's the angel,</i>

30
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:25,127
<i>spreading her wings to soar,
at this very moment.</i>

31
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:29,756
<i>Your smile is a ray of sun in the spring.</i>

32
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:34,052
<i>You run and a gentle breeze follows.</i>

33
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:35,178
[sighs deeply]

34
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:38,181
[teacher] <i>Saeki,</i>

35
00:01:38,265 --> 00:01:40,434
- 98 points!
- [students exclaiming]

36
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:41,685
[teacher] You did a great job.

37
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,270
Thank you very much.

38
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:45,939
[girl] That's amazing!

39
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:48,025
Best grade in multiple subjects?

40
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:50,152
You're in your own league, Nanako.

41
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:51,653
[chuckles] It's nothing special.

42
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:53,363
- See? Look at mine.
- Really?

43
00:01:53,447 --> 00:01:55,449
[boy] <i>You are special!</i>

44
00:01:56,867 --> 00:02:00,287
<i>Your intelligence is
like a beautiful pearl...</i>

45
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,248
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

46
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:12,799
- Hey!
- Hey, stop!

47
00:02:12,883 --> 00:02:13,967
52 points?

48
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:16,928
Come on, you gotta do better than that.

49
00:02:17,012 --> 00:02:19,222
All that reading, for what? [laughs]

50
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,933
What is this weird book anyway?

51
00:02:22,017 --> 00:02:23,226
<i>The Flowers of Evil!</i>

52
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:24,936
It's Baudelaire!

53
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,105
As if you'd understand its excellence!

54
00:02:27,189 --> 00:02:29,691
You're looking down on me, aren't you?

55
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:32,235
[teacher] Nakamura.

56
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:36,740
Nakamura!

57
00:02:37,449 --> 00:02:38,867
Answer me. Respond! [bangs table]

58
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:39,993
[Sawa] Yeah, I'm here.

59
00:02:45,749 --> 00:02:48,377
Nakamura, you got
the worst grade in class.

60
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:51,421
Zero points.

61
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,257
Explain yourself.

62
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:58,387
Why did you leave all the answers blank?

63
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:03,100
Say something! [bangs table]

64
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,228
Once you're in the real world,
you won't get--

65
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,312
Shut up,

66
00:03:07,813 --> 00:03:08,855
you shit bug.

67
00:03:10,107 --> 00:03:11,692
[♪ dramatic rock music playing]

68
00:03:17,781 --> 00:03:19,741
You are speaking to your teacher.

69
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:23,036
How dare you call me "shit bug"!

70
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:35,799
Come to the faculty room
after school. Understood?

71
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:36,883
All right.

72
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:39,511
Next... Muraoka!

73
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:40,887
Come on. Hurry up!

74
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:48,437
[friend 1] Nakamura's insane!

75
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,730
Like, you don't know what she's thinking.

76
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:52,983
- [friend 2] She gives me the creeps.
- Right?

77
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,110
[boy] Honestly, it was a bit refreshing.

78
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,862
Seeing Shimoyama shaking and all.

79
00:03:56,945 --> 00:04:00,115
Man, I'd never want to date
a girl like that.

80
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:01,533
- [chuckling] Agreed.
- What?

81
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:03,785
Why are you acting superior?

82
00:04:03,869 --> 00:04:06,455
- No one would want to date you.
- [chuckling] Good point.

83
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:09,124
How dare you. You're no better than me!

84
00:04:09,207 --> 00:04:10,584
What? No, that's not true!

85
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,711
I... I read books!

86
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:15,172
You think you can understand literature?

87
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:18,383
Reading books doesn't
make you special or anything!

88
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:21,678
Besides, no one has even noticed!

89
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:25,098
Wait...

90
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:28,643
I forgot my book.

91
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:30,353
I'm gonna go get it.

92
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:32,022
- Hey, are you running away?
- No!

93
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:34,316
- I really forgot it!
- [friend 1] Hey, you wimp!

94
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,650
[friend 2] He totally ran away.

95
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:57,255
<i>I suppose...</i>

96
00:04:58,048 --> 00:05:00,175
<i>Saeki hasn't noticed</i>

97
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:02,636
<i>that I'm reading a book like this.</i>

98
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:05,347
[clattering]

99
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,400
SAEKI

100
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:18,860
[gasps softly]

101
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:24,324
Her gym clothes...

102
00:05:27,118 --> 00:05:30,455
[breathing heavily]

103
00:05:35,377 --> 00:05:37,003
[breath trembling]

104
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:38,797
[thumping sound]

105
00:05:39,548 --> 00:05:41,383
[gulps]

106
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:47,222
[thumping stops]

107
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,975
<i>Idiot! What am I thinking!</i>

108
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:54,396
<i>My feelings for Saeki are honorable.</i>

109
00:05:55,105 --> 00:05:56,523
<i>They're pure.</i>

110
00:05:57,315 --> 00:05:59,401
<i>I don't have any sinful thoughts...</i>

111
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:03,738
<i>at all.</i>

112
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:06,199
<i>Not a bit.</i>

113
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:11,746
<i>There's no way.</i>

114
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:25,302
<i>I don't have any immoral desires.</i>

115
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:27,929
<i>I definitely...</i>

116
00:06:29,264 --> 00:06:30,432
<i>Definitely...</i>

117
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:33,560
<i>Definitely...</i>

118
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:47,324
[♪ bright music playing]

119
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:48,867
Kasuga.

120
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:51,745
[chuckles]

121
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:53,121
[thumping sound]

122
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,217
- [music ends]
- [sniffs deeply]

123
00:07:10,347 --> 00:07:11,848
[breath trembling]

124
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:16,227
It smells like...

125
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:18,772
shampoo...

126
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:22,025
- [clang]
- [gasps]

127
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:25,904
[gasping] It's not like that!

128
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:39,417
[pants, screams]

129
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:48,259
[breathing heavily]

130
00:07:51,096 --> 00:07:52,806
- Takao?
- [gasps]

131
00:07:54,516 --> 00:07:55,517
It's not like that!

132
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:57,519
What are you talking about?

133
00:07:58,478 --> 00:07:59,729
Those books in your room!

134
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:01,856
You'd better clean them up!

135
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,110
[Takao gasping] No, no, no.

136
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:07,237
It was just a coincidence.

137
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:10,156
This was an unintentional accident.

138
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:12,617
[thumping sound]

139
00:08:25,964 --> 00:08:27,465
Like <i>The Flowers of Evil...</i>

140
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,301
for real...

141
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:37,475
[♪ opening theme music playing]

142
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:35,366
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

143
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:37,994
EPISODE 1

144
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,080
[sniffles]

145
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,374
[bang on table]

146
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:48,338
Saeki's gym clothes were missing
when she got to school this morning.

147
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:50,590
[students murmuring]

148
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:53,468
Does anyone know anything about this?

149
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:56,971
It's a pervert! Right, guys? Right?

150
00:09:57,555 --> 00:10:01,935
[teacher] If you know something,
make sure you come and tell me!

151
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:03,728
Understood?

152
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,147
[Takao] <i>I am a sinner.</i>

153
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,067
<i>I want to go somewhere far away.</i>

154
00:10:10,235 --> 00:10:12,362
<i>Somewhere... far away.</i>

155
00:10:14,531 --> 00:10:15,698
<i>But...</i>

156
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:20,120
<i>In this confined town,
there's nowhere I can run to.</i>

157
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:22,580
111.8 MILES TO THE SEA

158
00:10:23,665 --> 00:10:24,666
<i>Saeki...</i>

159
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:26,209
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

160
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:30,296
<i>I will atone for this sin
for the rest of my life.</i>

161
00:10:32,924 --> 00:10:34,509
<i>Even when I'm an old man.</i>

162
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:36,719
[screams]

163
00:10:38,263 --> 00:10:39,681
[Nakamura] What are you doing?

164
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:41,891
Huh?

165
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,893
[stuttering]

166
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:50,108
[chuckles weakly]

167
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:51,609
[Nakamura] By the way,

168
00:10:52,694 --> 00:10:56,406
you're always reading a book, aren't you?

169
00:10:56,781 --> 00:10:57,782
What?

170
00:10:58,533 --> 00:10:59,742
How do you know that?

171
00:11:00,285 --> 00:11:01,995
Because I sit behind you.

172
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:04,330
[Takao] Oh.

173
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:07,500
On top of that,
it's a weird book that nobody would know.

174
00:11:07,834 --> 00:11:08,835
Why is that?

175
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:11,671
Well...

176
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,549
I bet normal people
can't understand, but--

177
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,510
Wait. What?

178
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:19,220
What?

179
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:21,472
Give me a ride.

180
00:11:22,599 --> 00:11:24,767
To the other side of that mountain.

181
00:11:25,435 --> 00:11:26,436
What?

182
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:27,812
But, well, I mean...

183
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:29,439
[chuckling nervously] Why?

184
00:11:29,522 --> 00:11:30,648
Why?

185
00:11:30,732 --> 00:11:32,150
'Cause I want to go there.

186
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:34,068
What? Like...

187
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:37,113
You know, I have to go now, so-- [gasps]

188
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:39,073
Huh?

189
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,534
Kasuga.

190
00:11:42,911 --> 00:11:44,287
The thing is...

191
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:48,708
I saw you.

192
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:50,752
I saw you...

193
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:54,255
steal...

194
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:55,798
Saeki's gym clothes.

195
00:11:58,009 --> 00:11:59,677
[sniffs deeply]

196
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:01,846
It smells like...

197
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:04,599
shampoo...

198
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:06,684
What?

199
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:08,686
What?

200
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:10,855
If you don't want me to tell everyone,

201
00:12:10,939 --> 00:12:12,106
you'd better get going.

202
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:24,827
[screaming]

203
00:12:24,911 --> 00:12:26,120
He ran away.

204
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:31,376
YOUNG BOY TURNS TO CRIME

205
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:32,669
[reporter on TV] <i>In recent years,</i>

206
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:35,421
<i>we've seen an increase
in heinous incidents by teenagers...</i>

207
00:12:35,505 --> 00:12:36,631
LONELINESS
INNER DEMONS

208
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:39,217
<i>...as juvenile crimes intensify.</i>

209
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:45,306
<i>Why are boys with no record
of delinquency committing such offences?</i>

210
00:12:45,682 --> 00:12:46,683
Takao.

211
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,268
What's wrong?

212
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:51,020
What? No, nothing.

213
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:57,110
<i>I'll turn myself in.</i>

214
00:12:58,695 --> 00:13:00,780
<i>Before Nakamura exposes me...</i>

215
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:02,991
<i>I'll confess my sins...</i>

216
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:06,411
<i>to Saeki herself.</i>

217
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:12,458
All right, then, some announcements.

218
00:13:12,542 --> 00:13:15,086
As I always say, you guys,

219
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:17,380
don't cause trouble.

220
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:20,925
[Takao] <i>Baudelaire...</i>

221
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:23,386
[bells chiming]

222
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:24,470
<i>...bestow strength</i>

223
00:13:25,013 --> 00:13:26,139
<i>upon me!</i>

224
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:28,057
Sir.

225
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:30,101
What is it, Kasuga?

226
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:37,400
Saeki.

227
00:13:38,693 --> 00:13:40,278
It's about your gym clothes.

228
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:42,530
I'm the one who took them.

229
00:13:43,865 --> 00:13:45,158
I'm sorry!

230
00:13:48,578 --> 00:13:50,038
Kasuga...

231
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,425
You've told me the truth...

232
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,177
Thank you.

233
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:09,766
[teacher clapping]

234
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:20,193
Kasuga...

235
00:14:21,069 --> 00:14:22,945
you're a true man of virtue.

236
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:27,575
All right, that's all.

237
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:32,955
[groans in frustration] <i>It's impossible!</i>

238
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:35,416
<i>How could I turn myself in?</i>

239
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:48,137
COME TO THE LIBRARY AFTER SCHOOL
DON'T RUN AWAY TODAY

240
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:02,318
LIBRARY

241
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,237
[Sawa] Why did you run away yesterday?

242
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:07,406
That must mean you don't mind
if I tell everyone, right?

243
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:09,408
No, it doesn't!

244
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,872
You spineless coward.

245
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:18,793
Filthy rat!

246
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:20,628
[shudders]

247
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:26,759
[stuttering] I wasn't trying to steal it!

248
00:15:27,969 --> 00:15:30,596
I just ended up taking it home,

249
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:33,432
- I meant to give it back and apologize--
- [Nanako] Kasuga?

250
00:15:33,516 --> 00:15:35,893
What? [gasps]

251
00:15:37,145 --> 00:15:39,397
You wanted to talk?

252
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,690
What?

253
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:43,151
Well... I...

254
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:46,195
[Sawa] Kasuga,

255
00:15:47,113 --> 00:15:49,907
don't you have
something important to tell her?

256
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:51,200
What?

257
00:15:51,284 --> 00:15:52,785
By any chance,

258
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,705
do you know something...

259
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:57,957
about my gym clothes?

260
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:00,042
No! Well, you see--

261
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:06,215
[Takao exclaims]

262
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,093
[exclaims]

263
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:13,681
[gasps, exclaims] Sorry!

264
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:31,657
Way to go, Kasuga.

265
00:16:31,741 --> 00:16:33,618
You went dead center.

266
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:35,369
What?

267
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:38,873
[breath trembling]

268
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:39,957
I'm ruined...

269
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:44,921
Why would you do that?

270
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,133
Tell me,

271
00:16:49,217 --> 00:16:50,760
how do you feel right now?

272
00:16:52,762 --> 00:16:55,223
Write me an essay
about how you feel right now.

273
00:16:55,932 --> 00:16:57,183
An... an essay?

274
00:16:58,059 --> 00:16:59,685
What the heck do you mean?

275
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:01,145
By tomorrow.

276
00:17:02,063 --> 00:17:03,606
See you after school.

277
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:10,071
No way I'd ever write that...

278
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,114
[ticking]

279
00:17:15,910 --> 00:17:17,745
[sniffles quietly]

280
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:24,543
[groans in frustration] <i>How?</i>

281
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:27,338
<i>How did I end up in this situation?</i>

282
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:29,549
[screams in frustration]

283
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:32,718
SECOND YEAR, CLASS ONE

284
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:35,137
[indistinct chatter]

285
00:17:40,518 --> 00:17:42,019
- Maeda.
- Maeda.

286
00:17:42,103 --> 00:17:43,396
Muraoka.

287
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:44,605
Hey, everybody!

288
00:17:44,689 --> 00:17:47,984
Teach is gonna get the police involved
about Saeki's gym clothes!

289
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:49,860
It's a serious case now! How crazy!

290
00:17:49,944 --> 00:17:51,654
Hey, cut it out, Yamada!

291
00:17:52,655 --> 00:17:54,532
I'm sorry, Nanako.

292
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:55,616
Ignore him.

293
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:56,701
Yeah.

294
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:06,335
[breath trembling]

295
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:10,339
[students vocalizing in distance]

296
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:14,885
Come on, show me the essay.

297
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:19,682
You don't have it?

298
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:32,194
What's that?

299
00:18:33,988 --> 00:18:35,573
A book of poems by Baudelaire.

300
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:37,408
<i>The Flowers of Evil.</i>

301
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:40,286
It's the book I love the most.

302
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:42,538
What?

303
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:47,043
Dark emotions billow throughout this book.

304
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:50,463
It's philosophy that people
in this town could never understand.

305
00:18:50,546 --> 00:18:53,799
Baudelaire took the malice
all of us secretly harbor

306
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:56,177
and spelled it all out in this book!

307
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:59,347
This is who I am.

308
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:02,308
This is my ess--

309
00:19:03,893 --> 00:19:06,020
Shut it, shit bug.

310
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:08,522
I was expecting...

311
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:09,982
[yelling] ...a messy...

312
00:19:10,066 --> 00:19:11,525
and gushy...

313
00:19:11,609 --> 00:19:14,487
exhibition of your true self, Kasuga.

314
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:17,823
I wanted you to spill out
everything in this essay!

315
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:22,244
You buried your face in Saeki's boobs,

316
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:25,498
sniffed her gym clothes over and over,

317
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:29,919
and rubbed them
all over your body, didn't you?

318
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:32,755
You know that you're a total,
utter pervert, Kasuga!

319
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:36,592
[grunts] What the heck?

320
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:38,010
This doesn't make any sense!

321
00:19:38,094 --> 00:19:40,638
What's wrong with you, Nakamura?

322
00:19:40,721 --> 00:19:42,973
[breathing heavily] I... I'm not.

323
00:19:43,057 --> 00:19:46,227
I didn't rub them all over my body!

324
00:19:47,770 --> 00:19:50,773
Saeki is my goddess!

325
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:54,694
She's my muse, my femme fatale,
my Mary, and my Venus.

326
00:19:54,777 --> 00:19:56,070
She will be, forever!

327
00:19:59,699 --> 00:20:03,119
I'll burn this damned thing
in the incinerator!

328
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,498
[gasps]

329
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:08,582
[grunts]

330
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:10,626
[groans]

331
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,131
What the!

332
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,259
By the way, that thing we talked about...

333
00:20:18,801 --> 00:20:20,094
my big brother has one.

334
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:21,595
- [Saeki] Hey guys...
- Seriously?

335
00:20:21,679 --> 00:20:23,472
[Nanako] Do you know where Kasuga is?

336
00:20:23,556 --> 00:20:26,016
- Oh... Kasuga?
- Yeah.

337
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:27,727
No clue.

338
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:30,521
Okay. Thanks. Bye. [chuckles]

339
00:20:31,939 --> 00:20:34,191
What? Hey, wait! What?

340
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:35,401
Stop it!

341
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:38,362
What?

342
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:41,323
Wait, stop!

343
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:42,408
[grunts]

344
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:44,869
[♪ soft music playing]

345
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:52,376
Ah!

346
00:20:53,544 --> 00:20:54,712
[groans]

347
00:20:58,841 --> 00:21:02,803
Ah! No! Somebody!

348
00:21:03,721 --> 00:21:04,889
Ah!

349
00:21:06,182 --> 00:21:08,434
Do you want people to see this?

350
00:21:09,477 --> 00:21:10,478
[shudders]

351
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:21,614
LIBRARY - CLOSED

352
00:21:21,697 --> 00:21:23,073
[Takao struggling]

353
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:27,244
Hey, wait! [groaning]

354
00:21:27,328 --> 00:21:29,371
Wait! [screams]

355
00:21:33,918 --> 00:21:37,087
[Takao groaning, gasping]

356
00:21:37,171 --> 00:21:40,299
Hey, wait! Stop! [screams]

357
00:21:42,259 --> 00:21:43,677
[gasps]

358
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:46,806
[panting]

359
00:21:51,352 --> 00:21:53,062
This...

360
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:56,482
is your true self. Isn't it, Kasuga?

361
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:01,695
Fine.

362
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:04,865
I won't tell anyone.

363
00:22:06,367 --> 00:22:07,451
Because, Kasuga,

364
00:22:07,952 --> 00:22:09,578
you're special.

365
00:22:11,455 --> 00:22:12,706
Special?

366
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:16,836
In return...

367
00:22:20,047 --> 00:22:21,215
I want you...

368
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:24,677
to make a contract with me.

369
00:22:25,386 --> 00:22:26,512
What?

370
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:31,642
A contract?

371
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:48,325
[♪ music peaks, fades]

372
00:22:48,409 --> 00:22:50,744
TO BE CONTINUED

373
00:22:50,828 --> 00:22:52,830
[♪ closing theme music playing]

374
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:48,886
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

375
00:23:48,969 --> 00:23:51,722
[narrator] <i>Kasuga agrees
to a mysterious contract.</i>

376
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:53,057
<i>Through a twist of fate,</i>

377
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:55,684
<i>he manages to score
a date with Saeki, but...</i>

378
00:23:56,435 --> 00:23:57,978
<i>Next time, on episode two.</i>

379
00:23:58,062 --> 00:24:00,981
<i>The contract with Nakamura
weighs heavily on Kasuga.</i>

380
00:24:01,065 --> 00:24:02,816
Translated by Yuka Kristi
